\item\textbf{Prove that all points have the same distance $\sqrt{2}$}

Given: The points $P_1 ,\dots, P_n\in\mathbb{R}^{n-1}$ are:
\[
P_i = e_i = (0,\dots,0, 1,0,\dots, 0),\quad\quad P_j = e_j = (0,\dots,0, 1,0,\dots, 0)
\]

Difference between two points: $\Delta d = P_i - P_j =  e_i - e_j$

This vector has:
\begin{itemize}
\item at position $i$: $1$,
\item at position $j$: $-1$,
\item otherwise $0$
\end{itemize}

Norm:
\[
\parallel P_i - P_j\parallel^2 = (1)^2 + (-1)^2 = 2\Rightarrow\parallel P_i - P_j\parallel =\sqrt{2}
\]

$\to$ All points have the same distance from each other.

